[4] USA (Minnesota)
Date: Tue 29 Mar 2011
Source: SixNews, kaaltv.com [edited]
http://kaaltv.com/article/stories/S2041297.shtml?cat=10151


The measles spike has grown in Minnesota. The Minnesota Department of
Health now confirms 13 cases. Those affected range in age from 4
months to 34 years. Six cases were children who are old enough to have
been vaccinated but haven't been. The Health Department believes the
outbreak started with an infant who returned from Kenya.

