[7] Canada (Ontario)
Date: Wed 30 Mar 2011
Source: Community Press, QNI Agency [abbreviated & edited]
http://www.communitypress-online.com/ArticleDisplay.aspx?e=3049793


The Hastings and Prince Edward Counties Health Unit has confirmed a
case of measles in a young student in Hastings County. Unit staff said
in a press release they are investigating where the child may have
contracted the illness and are taking steps to prevent it from
spreading to others. "Since the immunization rate in Ontario is high,
the risk to the general public is considered low," said the release,
reporting a 92 per cent immunization rate among school-age children.

"The health unit is recommending that individuals born after 1970,
who have not been immunized with the MMR vaccine, receive the vaccine
through their family doctor or through a health unit immunization
clinic," said the release. "Those born before 1970 likely had measles
in childhood, and are, therefore, protected."

Updates on the measles situation will be posted on
http://www.yourhealthunit.ca.

[The adjacent counties of Hastings and Prince Edward can be located
in the map of the counties of Ontario at
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Census_divisions_of_Ontario. - Mod.CP]

